# HTML & CSS

## HTML

- Semantic HTML5 (`main`, `section`, `header`, `footer`)
- Meaningful `id`/`class` names describing content, not appearance
- SEO meta tags and `aria-*` attributes where needed
- Proper heading hierarchy (single `h1`, then `h2`, `h3`…)

## CSS

- CSS custom properties for theming and color schemes
- Mobile-first responsive design; flexbox and grid for layout
- Keep specificity low; avoid deep nesting
- Group related styles together

## Accessibility

- Sufficient color contrast; visible focus styles for keyboard nav
- Alt text on images; test keyboard-only navigation

## Performance

- `preconnect` for external fonts/resources
- Small, focused CSS file; optimize critical rendering path

## Progressive Enhancement

- Core content readable without JavaScript
- Dark mode via CSS custom properties; respect system preferences when possible
